# Build context exclusions for `az acr build` / `docker build`.
# Keeps the upload small + safe. The image only needs the two addon
# directories + infra/docker/. Everything else here is noise or sensitive.
#
# IMPORTANT: directory patterns have NO trailing slash. .dockerignore's
# matcher (Go filepath.Match) treats `.claude/` as a literal path ending in
# `/` — which never exists — so it matches nothing. `.claude` (no slash)
# correctly excludes the directory and its entire subtree. This differs from
# .gitignore, where trailing slashes are conventional.

# ── Version control ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ── Claude / agent worktrees + session data ──────────────────────────────────
# CRITICAL: .claude/worktrees/ holds ~20 full copies of the repo. Excluding
# this is the single biggest context-size win — without it the build context
# is multi-GB and `az acr build` spends ~an hour just packing the tar.
.claude

# ── Terraform — infra-as-code never belongs in the app image ────────────────
# Note: infra/docker/ is NOT excluded — the Dockerfile COPYs from it.
infra/terraform

# ── Python bytecode + virtualenvs ────────────────────────────────────────────
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.venv
**/venv

# ── Node — node_modules is huge; the committed dist/ is what ships ──────────
**/node_modules

# ── Logs, plans, local state ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.log
**/*.tfplan
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*

# ── Local secrets / env files ────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.tfvars
!**/*.tfvars.example
**/.env
**/.env.*

# ── OS / editor cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.swp
**/*~

# ── Odoo local runtime data (if any exists from local dev) ──────────────────
**/filestore
**/sessions

# ── Local-only scratch / output dirs ────────────────────────────────────────
# `outputs/` and `work/` are local-dev scratch folders (PowerPoint exports,
# notebook outputs, etc.). They never belong in the image AND PowerPoint's
# exclusive lock on its `~$*` temp files causes `az acr build` to fail with
# Permission denied while tarring the build context.
outputs
work

# ── Office / Word / Excel / PowerPoint lock + author files ──────────────────
# Office apps create `~$<filename>.docx` etc. while a doc is open, with an
# exclusive lock that `az acr build` cannot read. `.pptx`/`.docx`/`.xlsx`
# files at the repo root are documentation, not app artifacts.
**/~$*
**/*.pptx
**/*.docx
**/*.xlsx

# ── pnpm content-addressed store (Windows) ──────────────────────────────────
.pnpm-store

# ── This file + the Dockerfile itself ────────────────────────────────────────
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
